        "title": "feat(cron): add webhookAllowPrivateNetwork opt-in to bypass SSRF guard for cron webhook POSTs",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- **Problem:** After the SSRF hardening from CVE-2026-27488 / GHSA-w45g-5746-x9fp, `delivery.mode: webhook` jobs targeting `127.0.0.1` or private-network addresses are blocked. `tools.web.fetch.allowPrivateNetwork` does not apply to the cron webhook path.\n- **Change:** Add an optional `cron.webhookAllowPrivateNetwork` config key (default `false`). When set to `true`, all cron-related webhook POSTs — job completion delivery, failure alerts, failure destinations, and the deprecated `notify + cron.webhook` fallback — pass `{ allowPrivateNetwork: true }` to `fetchWithSsrFGuard`. Default behavior is unchanged.\n- **Refactor:** Extracted webhook notification logic into `src/gateway/server-cron-notifications.ts` and a shared `postCronWebhook` helper, reducing duplication across delivery/failure paths.\n- **Schema:** Added `webhookAllowPrivateNetwork` to the Zod schema and regenerated the config baseline checksum.\n- **Sync with main:** Branch was rebased onto current `openclaw/main`. The static `src/config/schema.base.generated.ts` has been removed upstream in favor of Zod (`src/config/zod-schema.ts`) and the `pnpm config:docs:gen`-generated `docs/.generated/config-baseline.sha256`; conflicts were resolved against the new structure and the baseline was regenerated.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm config:docs:check` passes.\n- `pnpm test src/gateway/server-cron.test.ts` (14 tests) passes.\n- `pnpm test src/config/schema.base.generated.test.ts` passes.\n\n## Security note\n\nStill an explicit opt-in. Operators should only enable this when they accept that cron jobs may POST to loopback or private-network addresses.",
